# Ollama model definition for the harness (branch beta_qwen3coder, issue #123).
#
# This branch runs a ~3B Qwen2.5-Coder in place of VibeThinker-3B. The official
# Ollama library tag is used directly, so a Modelfile build is OPTIONAL — the
# default config (vibeharness/config.py) points at `qwen2.5-coder:3b-instruct`,
# which you just pull:
#
#     ollama pull qwen2.5-coder:3b-instruct        # ~1.9 GB (Q4_K_M), fits 8 GB GPU
#
# ⚠️ 3B-PARITY: there is NO dense ~3B *Qwen3-Coder* — that line is MoE only (smallest
# 30B-A3B, then 80B-A3B "Next", then 480B-A35B), which breaks apples-to-apples parity
# with the 3B-dense VibeThinker and won't fit an 8 GB card. Qwen2.5-Coder-3B-Instruct
# is the closest true ~3B dense coder (VibeThinker itself derives from Qwen2.5-(Coder-)3B).
# See QWEN3CODER_ANALYSIS.md / QWEN3CODER_DIVERGENCE.md.
#
# Build a custom-named copy with:  ollama create vibe-qwen3coder -f Modelfile
# The harness sets sampling parameters (temperature, top_p, top_k, num_ctx, num_gpu)
# per request, so this only needs to point at the weights.
FROM qwen2.5-coder:3b-instruct
